Pre Requisites: (For linux distro)

  Node.js

    Angular requires a current, active LTS, or maintenance LTS version of Node.js.
    >> sudo apt-get update
    >> sudo apt-get install nodejs
  
    Check node js installation by following commands

    >> node -v
  npm
  
    Install node package manager 

    >> sudo apt-get install npm.

    Check npm installation by following command. it gives version of npm

    >> npm -v
Install the Angular CLI
  You use the Angular CLI to create projects, generate application and library code, and perform a variety of ongoing development tasks such as testing, bundling, and deployment.

  To install the Angular CLI, open a terminal window and run the following command:
  
  >> npm install -g @angular/cli
  
Voila! Now you have created environment to build angular projects. 
  
  
 
  

